label: NA
definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing information about the originating source datasets from Monitoring Programs for the Stream Habitat Metric Integration project. This table corresponds to the RecordLevel table in the database (.accdb) file.

label: bibilographicCitation
definition: A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.

label: datasetID
definition: A unique identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.

label: datasetLink
definition: A URL identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. The source location for the originating source data.

label: datasetName
definition: The name of the originating data set from which the record was derived.

label: type
definition: The nature or genre of the resource. The type of data obtained from the originating dataset, including water chemistry (including but not limited to pH) and physical habitat (including but not limited to channel dimensions and characteristics).
examples: Water Quality and Physical Habitat Structure

label: institutionCode
definition: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label: metadataID
definition: A URL identifier for the metadata for the originating source dataset.

label: modified
definition: The most recent calendar date on which the datasets were modified or combined as part of the integrated dataset.

label: preProcessingCode
definition: URL identifier for access to the code used to pre-process (download, standardize and tidy) the data sets before integration into the Stream Habitat Integrated Dataset.

label: projectCode
definition: The acronym of the name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from wich the source data originates from.

label: projectName
definition: The name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from wich the source data originates from.
examples: USFS PacFish/InFish Biological Opinion Monitoring Program
